requests.name: Companies
requests.docs:
This is a paged endpoint, used to display data on the admin portal. Slightly different from other paged endpoints, defaults to 15 results per page and returns items by ModifiedAt in descending order. This endpoint does not return full response objects. 

## Request query params
`page_token` this is the token to inform the api to know where to fetch the next records. This token is acquired from the first response body as seen below. If left empty the api fetches only the first 15 records.

## Request body
`None`

## Response (with companies)

```json
{
  "companies": [
    {
      "id": "1cabafee-6c4e-4ba4-b408-40148e8768cc",
      "name": "Smallville",
      "email": "cleophasbarwareng@ids.company",

      "status": "Pending",
```
